I read [CONF-9343|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-9343] and my guess is that the solution that was mentioned there was implemented as:
{noformat}
LuceneSearcherImpl:search - Error encounterd in lucene search: maxClauseCount is set to 1024
{noformat}

I'm looking through our logs and I see *tens of thousands* of log messages like this *per day*.

I don't want to change the log level for the entire LuceneSearcherImpl class, I just want this particular warning not to be displayed.

As far as I understand the problem, there isn't anything that can be done about this error, so why should we be bothered with useless warnings? 

Can you display the warning at a lower logging level?

thanks,
Igor

