Confluence uses Australian-English variants of words, rather than the US spellings, in all but one case - the {color} macro.

This makes it stand out - especially on pages such as [Color Text Macro|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Color+Text+Macro], where it is explained that 'you can use the {color} macro to change the colour of a block of text.'

A nice improvement would be to allow users to enter either variant of the word in the wiki text, according to their preference.

i.e.:
{noformat}{colour:red}text{colour}{noformat}
would have the same effect as:
{noformat}{color:red}text{color}{noformat}
